@hebasto: This seems like a good place for some context to translators. For example, look at the French translation below.
![Screen Shot 2021-03-18 at 7 49 37 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23396902/111712139-6d111100-8823-11eb-8bdf-97ea107f9cd5.png)
 I don't know how the decimal unit `kB` is written in French (**Edit:** It's written as `ko`), but how do we let a translator know that they are supposed to translate as the`decimal unit` and not the `binary unit`?

